18
00:01:03,210 --> 00:01:05,810
早上好  芬奇
Good morning, Finch.

19
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:11,320
你都不敲门的吗
Don't you knock?

20
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:12,650
没必要就不敲
Not if I can help it.

21
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:17,460
戳穿了你的身份  我感到很内疚
I felt bad about blowing your cover identity.

22
00:01:17,460 --> 00:01:19,790
我在给你找新工作
Been looking for a new job for you.

23
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:23,230
你可以去遛狗  或是去弹钢琴
Dog walker, maybe. Or concert pianist?

24
00:01:26,070 --> 00:01:28,670
我有工作  里瑟先生  你也有
I have a job, Mr. Reese, and so do you.

25
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,140
机器又发来一个新的数字
The machine has sent us a new number.

26
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,580
他名叫乔伊・杜班
His name's Joey Durban,

27
00:01:39,580 --> 00:01:42,120
107步兵团的士兵
A soldier in the 107th infantry,

28
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:44,470
刚从阿富汗回来
Just back from Afghanistan.

29
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:48,090
陆军奖章
Army commendation medal,

30
00:01:48,090 --> 00:01:49,690
紫心勋章
purple heart--

31
00:01:49,690 --> 00:01:50,860
这家伙骁勇善战啊
Guy was a fighter.

32
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:51,970
跟你一样
Just like you.

33
00:01:52,170 --> 00:01:54,860
我在伊拉克和107步兵团并肩战斗过
I fought besiade the 107th in Iraq.

34
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:56,770
大多数还都是孩子
Most of them were just kids.

35
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:00,100
参军的原因多半是因为
Joined up because they lost family or friends

36
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,300
911的时候失去了亲人或朋友
when the towers came down.

37
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:03,740
他们在伊拉克要么早早地成熟
Over there, they grew up fast.

38
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:05,740
要么早早地牺牲了
Or they died.

39
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:07,740
不管怎么说乔伊活着回来了
Well, at least Joey came home alive.

40
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:10,220
现在你得帮他继续保持下去
And now you can help him stay that way.

41
00:02:11,290 --> 00:02:14,250
他在市中心的一座大楼做门童
He works as a doorman at a building in midtown.

42
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,680
我这就去
I'm on it.

43
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:17,650
按照标准的操作程序
Standard operating procedure--

44
00:02:17,650 --> 00:02:21,020
我会克隆他的手机截取通话和短信
I'll clone his phone for voice and texts.

45
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,220
我会跟踪他
I'll start following him.

46
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:24,090
另外  芬奇
And, uh, Finch...

47
00:02:24,090 --> 00:02:25,430
如果你要开夜车
If you're going to work all night,

48
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:28,160
就得多锻炼身体了
you should try getting some exercise.

49
00:02:37,470 --> 00:02:39,910
你看上去美极了  杰太太
You look fabulous, Mrs. J.

50
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:44,060
真想约您出去  不过我得先打败拉瑞・希格才行
I'd ask you out myself, but I'd have to fight off Larry Siegel.

51
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,820
你嘴真甜
Thank you.

52
00:02:46,780 --> 00:02:48,380
你好
Hello.

53
00:02:55,690 --> 00:02:58,630
罗比  我得早点下班
Robbie, I got to take off early.

54
00:03:03,330 --> 00:03:06,810
乔伊和一个叫琵娅・莫雷斯科的姑娘订婚了
Joey's engaged to a girl named Pia Moresco.

55
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:11,540
他出征时  她等了他六年
She waited six years for him while he was deployed.

56
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:12,980
过来亲一个
Yeah, come here.

57
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:15,400
我爱你  乔伊
I love you, Joey.

58
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,860
喂  芬奇
Hey, Finch.

59
00:03:32,860 --> 00:03:34,400
芬奇  你在吗
Finch, are you there?

60
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,830
在  有什么问题吗
Yes. Is there a problem?

61
00:03:40,580 --> 00:03:41,540
你在干什么
What are you doing?

62
00:03:41,540 --> 00:03:43,100
没什么
Nothing.

63
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:45,810
你不是说好不骗我了吗
Thought you said you'd never lie to me.

64
00:03:45,810 --> 00:03:47,700
到底什么事  里瑟先生
What's the problem, Mr. Reese?

65
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,140
我们的目标  乔伊・杜班
Our guy, Joey Drban...

66
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:51,130
我已经跟了他八个小时了
I've been on him for eight hours, and all he's done

67
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:52,470
他除了帮老大妈开门
is open doors for old ladies,

68
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:54,240
就是在逛商店看橱窗
and now he's going window shopping.

69
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,710
既然机器给出了他的号码
If the machine's given us his number,

70
00:03:55,770 --> 00:03:57,640
那他就肯定有事
he must be caught up in something.

71
00:03:57,640 --> 00:04:00,040
他收到一条短信  有点像密码
He got a text, it's a bit garbled.

72
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,040
发过去了
Sending it over.

73
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:04,190
Anchor d-0
"Anchor d-0."

74
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:05,710
这是什么意思
This supposed to mean something?

75
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:06,590
我怎么不知道
I don't know.

76
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:07,780
你才是负责动脑的哎
You're the genius.

77
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:26,000
<font color="#4096d1">疑犯追踪 第1季 第3集</font>
