78
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:36,500
趴下  喂你  把门打开
Get down, get down. You, open the door now!

79
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,710
-我说了  趴下  -快走
- I said, "Get down!" - Go! Go!

80
00:04:38,770 --> 00:04:40,230
-趴下  -趴在地上
- Get down! - Get on the ground!

81
00:04:41,370 --> 00:04:43,760
趴下  你  快把门打开  快点
Down, down to the ground! You, open the door. Now.

82
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,790
我说了  趴下
I said, "Get down."

83
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:48,960
低下头
Head down.

84
00:04:48,970 --> 00:04:50,830
还有50秒
50 seconds!

85
00:04:52,930 --> 00:04:56,070
低下头  别看我
Head down. Don't look at me.

86
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,970
还有40秒
40 seconds!

87
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:04,110
伙计  别动歪脑筋
Not a good idea, pal.

88
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:08,180
还有30秒
30 seconds!

89
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:13,620
把钱都包好
Wrap it up!

90
00:05:16,810 --> 00:05:18,700
还有10秒  S  快走
10 seconds, Sierra. Move!

91
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:20,540
S  快点
Sierra, move!

92
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,880
够了
Enough!

93
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:36,950
我回来了  里瑟先生
I'm back, Mr. Reese.

94
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:39,430
我破译了那条短信  是个地址
I've deciphered that text-- it's a street address...

95
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:40,940
是家银行
for a bank.

96
00:05:41,330 --> 00:05:42,830
好吧  芬奇
No kidding, Finch.

97
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:45,730
刚才那段抱怨这家伙无聊的话
What I said about our guy being boring--

98
00:05:46,230 --> 00:05:50,270
我收回
I take it back.

99
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:05,420
女士们先生们  请注意保管好您的财物
Ladies and gentlemen, please do not leave bags unattended.

100
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:06,450
谨防扒窃
Unattended bags will be...

101
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:08,120
约翰
John.

102
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,170
我都不知道你从那边回来了
I didn't know you were back from over there.

103
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:16,290
洁西卡
Jessica.

104
00:06:18,030 --> 00:06:19,460
我没有  我只是
I'm not. I'm just...

105
00:06:19,470 --> 00:06:21,200
实际上是正要回去
Heading back, actually.

106
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,070
你的制服呢
Where's your uniform?

107
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:25,020
我找了份新工作
I got a new job.

108
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:28,640
还是那种问不得的工作吗
One of those jobs you can't talk about?

109
00:06:39,990 --> 00:06:42,720
这么说我们的那位乔伊是个银行劫匪
So our friend Joey's a bank robber.

110
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,860
所以机器才跳了他的号码吗
Is that why the machine gave us Joey's number?

111
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:47,260
我设计这个机器搜索致命的威胁
I built the machine to look for lethal intent.

112
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:50,360
武装抢劫不太可能跳出来
Armed robbery wouldn't normally make the cut.

113
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:53,460
不管怎样  我说直接把他交给纽约警局
Either way, I say we gift wrap him and give him to the NYPD

114
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,380
免得有人送命
before someone winds up dead.

115
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:57,440
芬奇  这小子是个好兵
Finch, the guy was a good soldier.

116
00:06:57,440 --> 00:07:00,340
至少让我查出他是怎么惹得一身骚
Let me at least find out how he got into this mess.

117
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:03,140
好吧  不过别让你的判断被情绪影响了
Okay, but don't let your personal feelings warp your judgment.

118
00:07:03,140 --> 00:07:05,540
又没人逼他去抢银行
No one forced him to go robbing banks.

119
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,710
等等  他和某人见面了
Hang on. He's meeting someone.

120
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,260
他给了她什么东西
He's giving her something.

121
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:14,600
好像是钱  好多钱
Looks like money-- a lot of money.

122
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:31,870
那么  另外这个女人是谁
So... who's the other woman?

123
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,160
还不知道她的名字
I don't know her name yet.

124
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:37,200
偷情的银行劫匪
Bank robber and a cheat.

125
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,450
听上去不会有好下场啊
Unlikely to have a happy ending.

126
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:42,070
你觉得他可能要杀其中一个女人吗
Do you think he's targeting one of the women?

127
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:43,470
有可能
Could be.

128
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:46,010
看来我只能亲自接近乔伊才能查清楚
Only way I'm going to find out is to get closer to Joey,

129
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:47,640
这可不容易
and that won't be easy.

130
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:50,180
这伙人组织严密  异常谨慎
These guys are organized and ultra-cautious.

131
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:52,280
之间没有不必要的联系
No unnecessary contact.

132
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:56,380
等等
Hang on.

133
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,040
这个的哥也是抢银行的
That cabbie was at the bank.

134
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:04,540
他是给他们跑腿的
Just made their courier.

135
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:07,940
芬奇  查下牌照是5V80的出租
Finch, run a check on cab medallion number 5-victor-80.

136
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:11,700
司机名叫威利斯
Driver's name is Willis, also an ex-soldier

137
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,100
也是107步兵团的退伍兵
in the 107th infanry.

138
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,600
和乔伊是一个部队的
Same unit as Joey.

139
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,270
也是一起抢劫的
And also a bank robber.

140
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:18,770
我入侵了出租车公司的网站
I hacked the taxi company website.

141
00:08:18,770 --> 00:08:20,500
在给乔伊送钱之前
Before he dropped the cash off with Joey,

142
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:22,040
威利斯开车去了一家在
Willis stopped at a bar in Coney Island

143
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,470
科尼岛的酒吧  叫绿色地带
Called the green zone.

144
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:28,050
酒吧主人是前士官长  山姆・拉蒂莫
Bar's owned by former master sergeant Sam Latimer,

145
00:08:28,050 --> 00:08:29,870
第一次海湾战争的退伍老兵
Veteran of the first gulf war.

146
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:33,090
看来我们找到团伙老大了
I think you just found the gang's ringleader.

147
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:35,690
我要接近拉蒂莫
I want to get close to Latimer.

148
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:37,090
帮我编个身份
And I'll need a cover story.

149
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,260
交给我吧
I'll get on that.

150
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:40,760
我还要你帮我在这团伙里...
And I need you to create a vacancy for me...

151
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,230
搞个空缺位子
With the gang.

152
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:44,930
这也不是问题
I'll get on that too.

153
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:46,800
还要什么吗
Anything else?

154
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,700
暂时没了
No, that'll do for now.

155
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,280
你是山姆・拉蒂莫吗
You Sam Latimer?

156
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:10,090
我是托尼・米勒
Name's Tony Miller.

157
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,560
一个在圣迭戈的陆战队哥们
Marine buddy down in San Diego,

158
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:17,330
告诉我说
Told me a while back,

159
00:09:17,330 --> 00:09:18,600
要是我来纽约
If I was ever in New York,

160
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,800
我就该来找你
I should look you up.

161
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:20,630
你那哥们叫什么名字
What's your buddy's name?

162
00:09:20,630 --> 00:09:22,010
赫克托・穆尼奥斯
Hector Munoz.

163
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:24,830
穆尼奥斯啊  我记得他  摩加迪休那会吧[索马里首都]
Munoz, yeah, I remember him from Mogadishu.

164
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:26,170
枪法不错  他怎么样
Good shooter. How's he doing?

165
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:27,640
不好
Not good.

166
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,770
他在赫尔曼斯被简易炸弹炸到
Ran over an IED in Hellmans.

167
00:09:29,780 --> 00:09:32,310
死前还撑了整整一个星期
Lasted a whole week before he hit room temperature.

168
00:09:32,310 --> 00:09:33,510
愿他安息
Rest in peace.

169
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:35,680
真是个顽强的家伙
Tough son of a bitch.

170
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,980
这么说
So...

171
00:09:36,980 --> 00:09:38,750
你想找什么样的活计  保安吗
What kind of work are you looking for? Security?

172
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:41,360
我可不想打工赚钱
I'm not looking for wages.

173
00:09:42,010 --> 00:09:43,780
我只想搞大票的
I'm only interested in lump sums.

174
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:45,280
你有麻烦吗
You in trouble?

175
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,160
那是我的问题
That's my business.

176
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,690
你要找我帮忙  就是我的问题
You're making it mine.

177
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:52,300
我之前在提华纳干私活
I was working freelance in Tijuana.

178
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,670
有个任务黄了  有人不开心了
Job went south. People's feelings got hurt.

179
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:57,800
我得想办法离他们远点
I need to put some distance between me and them.

180
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:02,570
我有经验  也有技术
I've got some experience you could use--skills.

181
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:03,840
什么样的技术
What kind of skills?

182
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:06,910
你在柜台下面有把点45
You have a .45 under the counter,

183
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,310
